00:13:40,841 --> 00:13:43,743
We did a previous show with Shelma Rodriguez.

149
00:13:43,903 --> 00:13:44,623
Oh, right, yes.

150
00:13:44,683 --> 00:13:47,665
She opened up everyone's eyes.

151
00:13:48,265 --> 00:13:49,626
Exactly, yes.

152
00:13:49,646 --> 00:13:51,907
She's really dug in and learned a lot about that.

153
00:13:51,927 --> 00:13:52,347
Yes, she has.

154
00:13:52,787 --> 00:13:55,329
A lot of facts and a lot of good information was put out.

155
00:13:56,329 --> 00:13:58,811
That was the last show we did, actually.

156
00:14:00,792 --> 00:14:02,733
So, you know, another question.

157
00:14:05,809 --> 00:14:12,863
How do you know, as far as the rezoning, how do you know there was a large number of people against it?

158
00:14:12,943 --> 00:14:16,109
What gets you to believe that?

159
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:19,451
Well, obviously, all of my neighbors are concerned.

160
00:14:19,991 --> 00:14:27,094
But then Sheryl Rodriguez, who we were just talking about, started a change.org petition online.

161
00:14:27,994 --> 00:14:42,059
And actually, as of last week, we had 980 verified signatures against the rezoning and against what the administration in this town wants to do.

162
00:14:42,439 --> 00:14:43,820
I think that's a strong number.

163
00:14:45,826 --> 00:14:51,569
There has, and it isn't, there just hasn't been any community outreach.

164
00:14:52,669 --> 00:15:12,017
And there was a meeting we were sitting in when they had just started talking about this and Kit Collins said, oh, if we could have knocked on every door in the Salem Street area, I would have wanted to talk to every neighbor and hear what they had to say and whether they were behind this.

165
00:15:12,117 --> 00:15:13,818
Well, you know,

166
00:15:14,871 --> 00:15:26,115
put that in an RFP then and have this Innis company, if they're the be all end all to community design and planning, they should be doing that.

167
00:15:26,215 --> 00:15:27,295
Put that in the RFP.

168
00:15:27,335 --> 00:15:35,398
That is your job to take care of the people in this area of your city and make sure that they are heard.

169
00:15:37,908 --> 00:15:45,233
The one thing that they're overlooking is that we are an environmental justice neighborhood.

170
00:15:45,493 --> 00:15:55,880
And that means, and this was put in the letter from our attorney at Richmond APC, and that is we are a racially diverse neighborhood.

171
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:59,222
We are an economically diverse neighborhood.

172
00:15:59,622 --> 00:16:02,104
We are a multilingual neighborhood.

173
00:16:02,624 --> 00:16:06,347
And no notice or community outreach has been done in English

174
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:11,310
let alone other languages for those that don't speak English.

175
00:16:12,151 --> 00:16:12,931
And that's not right.

176
00:16:13,892 --> 00:16:20,537
And this Salem Street rezoning has been in place since, I believe, July of last year.

177
00:16:21,217 --> 00:16:23,759
And the residents are just learning about it.

178
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:25,000
And I find that crazy.

179
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:33,826
And the first community engagement didn't happen until after they received our letter from the law firm.

180
00:16:34,507 --> 00:16:35,728
So that tells you

181
00:16:36,568 --> 00:16:41,410
that all of the people that raised concerns, many people say, oh, we brought it up.

182
00:16:41,510 --> 00:16:42,451
We wrote a letter.

183
00:16:42,811 --> 00:16:44,692
We called the Community Development Board.

184
00:16:45,152 --> 00:16:55,196
No action was going to be done until they got that our environmentally justice neighborhood is unhappy and the people need to be represented.

185
00:16:55,836 --> 00:16:58,738
So I think at the end of the day, we can all agree

186
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:01,280
Salem needs a little facelift.

187
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:02,622
It needs some love, right?

188
00:17:03,924 --> 00:17:08,951
But they have not followed processes set forth in their own procedures.

189
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,840
They haven't done that.

190
00:17:10,860 --> 00:17:28,068
Therefore, by law, if you haven't notified abutters and if you haven't had community engagement, and it's not just one community engagement, one time at the elementary school, six months, seven months after you've already started the process, no.

191
00:17:28,588 --> 00:17:36,332
They have to go all the way back and start over from the beginning, and that is what we intend to make them do.

192
00:17:37,572 --> 00:17:43,555
There have been no traffic studies, no studies on the effect to the school enrollments.

193
00:17:43,655 --> 00:17:45,236
How is that going to affect it?

194
00:17:46,037 --> 00:17:51,800
No studies for safety, just our own safety in the neighborhood around fire and police.

195
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:57,483
They're saying you can go four to six stories high and with eight foot between the buildings.

196
00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:00,103
Now, does that make common sense?

197
00:18:00,223 --> 00:18:01,325
Our streets are old.

198
00:18:01,385 --> 00:18:02,827
We are an older neighborhood.

199
00:18:03,367 --> 00:18:04,148
Very narrow.

200
00:18:04,329 --> 00:18:11,318
Sometimes if, on my street, if you have two cars parked on either side, the fire truck really has to finagle.

201
00:18:11,499 --> 00:18:14,162
And I'm like, I hope that guy's a good driver.

202
00:18:15,103 --> 00:18:16,905
Difficult time getting down to Longstreet.

203
00:18:17,125 --> 00:18:17,805
Exactly.

204
00:18:17,825 --> 00:18:23,829
And there are just so many other problems around Salem Street area.

205
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:34,637
We are fortunate enough to have a trained engineer working with us, and we found out many, many things that need to take place.

206
00:18:36,098 --> 00:18:42,766
are not, and so we are bringing those all up together, and there will probably be another legal letter.

207
00:18:43,326 --> 00:18:52,836
But ultimately, we are interviewing attorneys for a class-action lawsuit regarding the Salem Street lack of process as defined by the law.

208
00:18:52,996 --> 00:18:57,782
It constitutes, from a couple of attorneys, a taking of land, if you will.

209
00:18:59,042 --> 00:19:03,484
And ultimately, above all other items, there's discrimination, right?

210
00:19:03,524 --> 00:19:05,965
We are an environmental justice neighborhood.

211
00:19:06,325 --> 00:19:07,425
We have certain rights.

212
00:19:07,525 --> 00:19:09,546
This isn't taking place in West Medford.

213
00:19:09,566 --> 00:19:10,506
Why is that, right?

214
00:19:10,546 --> 00:19:11,927
Why is nothing like this taking?

215
00:19:12,887 --> 00:19:19,509
So that is discrimination, and we intend, you know, to see where that can go, so.

